{"_id":"3DyexYtB1rSclTuD","name":"Paradox Lost","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Paradox Lost</p>\n<p>When you r oll a miss, you can take 1 spike to treat that roll as though you had rolled a 7-9.</p>\n<p>You can&rsquo;t use this move again until you Meltdown.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6RzNrYPcqJVZvhI0","name":"The Sorcerer","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"class","data":{"name":"","description":"<h2>The Sorcerer</h2>\n<p>Dungeon World has rules, someone told you once. Rules much grander, more beautiful, more real than any laws we know. Did they phrase it like a challenge? Or do you just break axioms of metaphysics for fun?</p>\n<p>Other people have to study their whole lives to even start to conceptualize the facets of the universe that you mold to your whim.</p>\n<p>But hey, I guess nobody said life was fair.</p>\n<p>But what&rsquo;s really not fair is the kind of reputation you develop for doing this kind of thing. So sometimes you don&rsquo;t get it quite right and you demolish the emperor&rsquo;s orchard. Twice. Whatever. Or when the sacred crown you found just disappeared because you accidentally unraveled some of reality, you guess. Or you shot fireballs out of your eyes and everyone thought that was gross</p>\n<p>These are just some of the side effects people have got to learn to accept. And, honestly, if you&rsquo;ve already broken all the rules of magic, I&rsquo;m sure changing peoples&rsquo; minds should be no problem.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Name</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Human: Hecate, Abaris, Medea, Solomon, Chandra, Storm, Rey, Eshu, Nkisi, Taishiyao</li>\n<li>Genasi: Khotta, Mariz, Almalik, Fuqtu, Vanri, Sha-karn, Son-liin, Arjun, Barqan, Yb&rsquo;Tayyar</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Look</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>BODY: Gnarled, Strange, Wiry, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>EYES: Haunting, Clear, Wild, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>HAIR: Stylish, Bizarre, Decorated hat, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>ROBES: Patched, Embroidered, Ostentatious, or _ ___________</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Gear</h2>\n<p>You start with these items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Dungeon Rations ( 5 uses, r ation, 1 weight), Uses l eft: ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏</li>\n<li>5 coins</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose your defenses:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Leather Armor ( 1 a rmor, w orn, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Bag of Books ( 5 uses, 1 weight), Uses l eft: 5 &amp; 2 Healing Potions (0 weight)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose your weapon:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ritual Dagger ( hand, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Staff ( close, two-handed, 1 weight)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose one:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Adventuring Gear (5 uses, 1 weight), Uses left: 5</li>\n<li>Healing Potion ( 0 weight)</li>\n<li>12 coins</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>The Sorcerer Moves</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Magical Soul\n<ul>\n<li>The tags should be broad descriptors, rather than, say, c lose or r each. They don&rsquo;t describe how or what you do so much as color what happens when you do it, or the power through which you do it. The sets of actions are intended to be limiting but also a source of creativity. If one of your tags is e arthen, you could alter the Fighter&rsquo;s armor to be rocky and hard, or you could alter a stone wall to be porous to water. If one of your tags is  iendish, you could control a goblin with your devilish magic to fight for you or control a sea of hellfire to part.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Create a Spell<br />\n<ul>\n<li>The player and GM should be clear about the stakes and the intended effects of the spell before the roll. A spell description includes one tag, one action, and any number of metamagic praxes. The &ldquo;instead of&rdquo; clauses of Metamagic are meant to be instructive for this move. Without applying the &ldquo;targets&rdquo; praxis from Metamagic, any spell the Sorcerer creates runs the risk of affecting additional and unintended people, even before it spirals out of control, for example.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Metamagic<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Adding metamagic makes a spell more complicated, and so adds a stacking penalty to the roll.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Meltdown<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Many of these options have been left intentionally open to combine Dungeon World&rsquo;s narrative first approach with a wild-magic kind of randomness.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Push It<br />\n<ul>\n<li>The Sorcerer can push themselves multiple times in one roll - e.g., if they would like to work magic at the edge of their perception and have that magic last for one day, they could take both the Scarred and the Sick debilities to do so (as long as they had not already taken those debilities). Note that if Scarred is taken, the penalty to CHA will apply to the roll to Create a Spell.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Use Magic Item<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Cursed magic items being maximized might mean that the curse lingers for a long while, perhaps indefinitely. Otherwise, the maximization might still be dangerous, but is probably beneficial to the Sorcerer.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Catastrophe<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Automatically here means that if the Sorcerer ever has the maximum number of spikes, they cannot ask to have retroactively triggered Catastrophe or etc - as soon as the Sorcerer gets their last spike, they make the Meltdown move.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Magic Battery<br />\n<ul>\n<li>If The Sorcerer has somehow come into a move that requires a place of power, they can use themselves if they have this move.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>A Mystery Wrapped in an Enigma<br />\n<ul>\n<li>The entity/GM character in question still chooses exactly what they want out of the Sorcerer&rsquo;s magical soul - the leverage is the soul, and however that might be interesting to the GM character is left to the GM to decide.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","races":{"0":{"label":"Human","description":"When you Meltdown, you take +1 forward to your next move."},"1":{"label":"Genasi","description":"Your soul has been touched by unfiltered elemental magic. You get an additional elemental tag for your Magical Soul."},"2":{"label":"???","description":""}},"alignments":{"0":{"label":"Chaotic","description":"Use magic without a plan or thought for the consequences."},"1":{"label":"Neutral","description":"Discover something about a magical mystery."},"2":{"label":"Good","description":"Directly aid another with your magic."},"3":{"label":"???","description":""}},"equipment":{"0":{"label":"You start with these items:","mode":"checkbox","items":["6JcOoZ8CNqYxLgyQ"]},"1":{"label":"Choose your defenses:","mode":"checkbox","items":["oGiXIqNQbukIjf06","iaxOPwJIrsnzGJWr","CMhNmAwhLVZk9lfq"]},"2":{"label":"Choose your weapon:","mode":"radio","items":["nMag6sXXRqc6SC4Q","xu45M9oglN3VEWHC"]},"3":{"label":"Choose one:","mode":"radio","items":["CMhNmAwhLVZk9lfq","YwHV7WYzTPSAOorl"]}},"hp":4,"load":8,"damage":"d4"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"7zZWhVSuuFXSdpBs","name":"Create A Spell","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Create A Spell (CHA)</p>\n<p>When you release your magic power, describe what you&rsquo;re trying to do using your magical tags and an action, then roll+CHA.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, it happens. Work out what that means with the GM. If it sounds like your spell should deal damage, deal your damage.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, it still happens but you take 1 spike and your magic puts you or somebody else in a spot, the GM will tell you how.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"starting","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":"<p>On a 7-9, it still happens but you take 1 spike and your magic puts you or somebody else in a spot, the GM will tell you how.</p>"},"success":{"value":"<p>On a 10+, it happens. Work out what that means with the GM. If it sounds like your spell should deal damage, deal your damage.</p>"}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"CHA","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9e1LqUS1yCZgYRUn","name":"Catastrophe","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Catastrophe</p>\n<p>You don&rsquo;t Meltdown until your fourth spike. When you vent pent-up magical energy, spend any number of spikes, then roll+spikes spent.</p>\n<p>On a hit, you explode with pure force inline with your Magical Soul&rsquo;s tags.</p>\n<p>Everyone and everything in the area takes damage as appropriate.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, you&rsquo;re safe from harm.</p>\n<p>You still automatically Meltdown as soon as you get your fourth spike.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":"<p>On a hit, you explode with pure force inline with your Magical Soul&rsquo;s tags.</p>\n<p>Everyone and everything in the area takes damage as appropriate.</p>"},"success":{"value":"<p>On a hit, you explode with pure force inline with your Magical Soul&rsquo;s tags.</p>\n<p>Everyone and everything in the area takes damage as appropriate.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, you&rsquo;re safe from harm.</p>"}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"BOND","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"DqtZFrey2tSqie2G","name":"Magic Battery","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Magic Battery</p>\n<p>You count as a place of power for the purpose of Rituals and other moves. Tell the GM who&rsquo;s interested in your power, and they&rsquo;ll tell you about someone else who&rsquo;s also interested.</p>\n<p>When someone taps into your magical power, roll+CON.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, you&rsquo;re fine and even have a little extra to spare - if someone was making a roll based on your power, they take +1.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, you take 2 spikes, but hold it together.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":"<p>On a 7-9, you take 2 spikes, but hold it together.</p>"},"success":{"value":"<p>On a 10+, you&rsquo;re fine and even have a little extra to spare - if someone was making a roll based on your power, they take +1.</p>"}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"CON","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FKsNsyB8gxqqFH4S","name":"Push It","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Push It</p>\n<p>You can power up your spells beyond normal limits. When you p ush yourself to Create a Spell, take a debility of your choice to upgrade one metamagic praxis.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Targets: push yourself to target up to three things.</li>\n<li>Duration: push yourself to have a spell last for up to a day.</li>\n<li>Range: push yourself to work magic at the edge of your perception.</li>\n<li>Potency: push yourself to deal +[[/r 2d4]] damage.</li>\n</ul>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FbKeFxGNYVz8N4Ze","name":"Amateur Expert","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Amateur Expert</p>\n<p>Take a move from the Bard, Immolator, or Wizard class l ists.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"RlkwPESIZduMM4OK","name":"Magical Soul","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Magical Soul</p>\n<p>Magic is a part of you, it&rsquo;s every part of you. You are a font of arcane power everflowing. Working with the GM, write the source of this magical power and pick two tags that describe what your magic is like (e.g. fiery and angelic could describe a sorcerer whose soul had been touched by the divine).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Write your choices here: ______________________________________________________________</p>\n<p>Then, pick a set of actions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your magic is blunt, forceful, and direct.\n<ul>\n<li>Use your magic power to push or pull, impress, or break</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Your magic is subtle, tricky, and perceptive<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Use your magic power to hinder or confuse, veil, or detect</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Your magic is defensive, physical, and helpful<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Use your magic power to protect or bolster, heal, or augment</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Your magic is creative, transformative, and commanding<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Use your magic power to shape o ralter, control, or conjure</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","choices":"","moveType":"starting","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"a4f39zfrRwLfJhdt","name":"You Need A Teacher","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>You Need A Teacher</p>\n<p>With their player&rsquo;s permission, choose another character. They become your mentor. Write a bond with them about that.</p>\n<p>They&rsquo;ll write a bond about how they think you should be using your powers. At the end of each session, if your mentor is impressed with you, take 1 xp.</p>\n<p>When your mentor Aids you and rolls a 10+ you clear 1 spike.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aSOPW1gYScBNmEQd","name":"Spell Eater","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Spell Eater</p>\n<p>When you absorb an ongoing magic spell or effect, roll+CON.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, you completely absorb the spell&rsquo;s energy and are healed of [[/r 1d8]] damage.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, you heal [[/r 1d4]] damage and choose one:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You must bear the brunt of the spell to absorb it.</li>\n<li>You absorb most of the spell, but some remains.</li>\n</ul>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":"<p>On a 7-9, you heal [[/r 1d4]] damage and choose one:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You must bear the brunt of the spell to absorb it.</li>\n<li>You absorb most of the spell, but some remains.</li>\n</ul>"},"success":{"value":"<p>On a 10+, you completely absorb the spell&rsquo;s energy and are healed of [[/r 1d8]] damage.</p>"}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"CON","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"esxCuYcYGgxjgVku","name":"Arcane Initiate","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Arcane Initiate</p>\n<p>Pick one spell of any level below your own.</p>\n<p>You can recreate that spell with Create a Spell, but you must choose one of your tags to color the spell.</p>\n<p>You can choose to use metamagic when you create that spell.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fMJOJLljKWeUrpjV","name":"Use Magic Item","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Use Magic Item</p>\n<p>When you activate or wield an enchanted or magical item, you can choose to have its effects maximized; it then runs out of power.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hHYkXEUhCDhRAw29","name":"Nuclear-Powered","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Nuclear-Powered</p>\n<p>While you have at least 1 spike, you deal +[[/r 1d4]] damage and have +1 armor.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jbMxffvHfuH0ge96","name":"Meltdown","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Meltdown</p>\n<p>When you get your third spike, mark xp, then roll [[/r 1d8]] to determine what your pent up magical energy wreaks. The GM will tell you what happens.</p>\n<p>1. Pure magical chaos, centered on you.</p>\n<p>2. Your magic seeps into the environment, giving it your tags and dangerous .</p>\n<p>3. One of your tags is corrupted, making it dangerous to use that tag to Create a Spell until the next time you Meltdown.</p>\n<p>4. Your magic creates an entity with one or more of your soul&rsquo;s tags.</p>\n<p>5. You take a debility of the GM&rsquo;s choice. Until you clear it, anyone you touch gets that same debility.</p>\n<p>6. One person present is permanently marked by your magic.</p>\n<p>7. Spells and magic items (including your own) react violently to you.</p>\n<p>8. You take [[/r 1d10]] damage and get 3 m agical armor that lasts for one day.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"starting","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mjHu1jI2Pb2RQzD1","name":"A Mystery Wrapped in an Enigma","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>A Mystery Wrapped in an Enigma</p>\n<p>When you Parley with a <strong>magical or extraplanar entity</strong>, you can always leverage your Magical Soul (the chance to study it, be invested with its power, wield it on their behalf, etc).</p>\n<p>The GM will tell you exactly what they want.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
