{"_id":"unm5aKNCWVsG2hLw","name":"Metamagic","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Metamagic</p>\n<p>You can feel the threads of magic, the weaves of arcane power that tie the world together. You can pluck them l ike strings. Pick one praxis you know:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Targets: your magic can target specific things instead of general areas.</li>\n<li>Duration: your magic can last for up to an hour, i nstead of only seconds.</li>\n<li>Range: your magic can act at a near d istance i nstead of close.</li>\n<li>Potency: your magic deals +[[/r 1d4]] damage.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When you describe a spell you&rsquo;re creating, you can add one or more praxes that you know. The first one is free, but you take -1 to Create a Spell for each praxis after the first.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"starting","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Sorcerer","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
